Starting off the week with a tip that has helped me get some of my cleanest glue ups. I used to spend so much time trying to close these little gaps at the jointer or the tablesaw. Sometimes I would just give up and use the force of my clamps to close them. If you can make them look almost perfect before you have to clamp them, you will have a much cleaner result and longer lasting joint. 
Give it a try, and let me know how it worked for you. 🤘🏼

The woman with 9 lives did it again and survived another bowel obstruction. My mom just spent the last 12 days between two hospitals, celebrated her 71st birthday with an NG tube, had chemo, multiple procedures to drain fluid… it’s been a freaking rollercoaster to say the least. But yesterday she finally got to come home, and we celebrated with a visit from two of her brothers who live out of state. And another one tomorrow! 

Late stage terminal ovarian cancer is a rollercoaster, and we are learning how quickly things can change. We are so glad to be able to welcome mom home to a fancy new electric chair and hope we bought ourselves more time with all our efforts. 🩷
